{"type":"message","id":"22bf0e27","parentId":"088cad17","timestamp":"2026-02-15T09:44:16.327Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Sun 2026-02-15 11:44 GMT+2] EVOLUTION FINAL PHASE: GITHUB APP & SKILLS DEPLOYMENT.\n\n1.  **GitHub App Audit:**\n    *   Read `docs_archive/github_documentation.json` (created in Phase 2).\n    *   Explain the role of a GitHub App (`arkadiy-bot-manager`).\n    *   List specific requirements for connection: App ID, Installation ID, Private Key (.pem), Client Secret (optional for server-to-server).\n    *   Benefits: Higher rate limits (5000/hr vs 60/hr), fine-grained permissions, \"Check Run\" status reporting.\n\n2.  **Skill Deployment (Action):**\n    *   Install selected skills:\n        `openclaw skills add pskoett/self-improving-agent`\n        `openclaw skills add openclaw/coding-agent`\n        `openclaw skills add oswalpalash/ontology`\n    *   *Note:* If `openclaw` CLI is not available in sandbox, simulate the installation via `write` to `skills/` directory or report as \"Ready to install via main process\".\n\n3.  **Self-Improvement Test (Simulation):**\n    *   Create a memory entry in `memory/evolution-log.md` utilizing the concept of `self-improving-agent`.\n    *   Log the \"Immunity\": \"PowerShell 'ls -F' conflict resolved via 'pwsh' enforcement. Anthropic dependencies removed via 'openclaw.json' cleanup.\"\n\n4.  **Report:**\n    *   GitHub App requirements list.\n    *   Skills installation status.\n    *   Confirmation of immunity log."}],"timestamp":1771148656325}}
